@Zuhayr Mohamed Thanks for commenting today!

You write, " I wonder why the graph only shows the ages of democratic nations. Does it have anything to do with the length of term served as leader of nation? "

You have a good point here. But I wonder if you can answer your own question here.  How would term limits affect the trajectory of this trend line?

@G. Bonnema thanks for participating today! You mention that almost all of the presidents are older than 40. That might be due to the Constitution mandating a minimum age  for being President (35). 

Do you think it is appropriate to mandate a minimum age to be President? What about a maximum age?

I wonder what if there are minimum age requirements to be head of government in other countries?  Or maximums?  How do you think those limits might affect the trend on this graph?

@Sam 
Hi Sam,
The point you made regarding Republican presidents being older than Democrat is interesting. It seems that Democrat candidates are much more progressive and change their views as times modernize. In the Republican Party, it appears that views tend to not modernize and the views stay the same. Interesting point!
